@startuml Componentes_AXIA

title Diagrama de componentes del sistema AXIA

skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 60
skinparam ranksep 80
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #333333
  FontSize 9
}
skinparam package {
  BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
  BorderColor #333333
  FontSize 10
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #333333
  FontSize 9
}

top to bottom direction

package "Frontend" as PRES {
  component "React Native · Expo\n(Vercel)" as Front
  component "Herramienta del Fabricante\n(Tkinter)" as Tool
}

package "Datos" as DATA {
  component "PostgreSQL\n(Supabase)" as DB
  component "IPFS\n(Pinata)" as IPFS
}

package "Backend · Render\n<<orientado a servicios>>" as BACK {
  component "main.py\nAPI REST · WebSocket\nauth · marketplace · subastas" as Main
  component "blockchain.py\nweb3.py · ABIs · gas" as BCPy
}

package "Blockchain · Polygon Amoy\n<<orientado a objetos>>" as CHAIN {
  component "WatchNFT" as NFT
  component "WatchMarketplace" as MKT
  component "WatchAuction" as AUC
  component "MockUSDC" as USDC
}

' Conexiones
Front --> Main      : REST / WebSocket
Tool  --> Main      : REST API

Main  --> DB        : SQL
Main  --> IPFS      : HTTP
Main  --> BCPy

BCPy  --> NFT       : "JSON-RPC "
BCPy  --> MKT       : "JSON-RPC  "
BCPy  --> AUC       : "JSON-RPC   "

note right of PRES
  React Native · Expo y la Herramienta del
  Fabricante también acceden directamente
  a los contratos vía JSON-RPC (ethers.js
  y web3.py respectivamente).
end note

' Layout
PRES  -[hidden]d-> DATA
PRES  -[hidden]d-> BACK
DATA  -[hidden]r-> BACK
BACK  -[hidden]d-> CHAIN

@enduml
